oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Vealy Scott Austin
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Perry Benjamin Austin of Finley, Tennessee carried this photograph of his wife, Vealy Scott Austin, with him while he served in Motor Truck Co. 536 in France during World War I. Austin served until June 1919. A mink trapper before the war, he ran a trolley car in Jackson after the war, and later worked as a carpenter. [See also GWjack001-GWjack010.]
